something that you feel you have to do because it is your moral or legal responsibility

data.chText: 把这事报告给警方是我的责任。
data.enText: It is my duty to report it to the police.

data.text: tax ♦ duty ♦ customs ♦ tariff ♦ levy ♦ excise

data.enText: These are all words for money that you have to pay to the government.
tax
money that you have to pay to the government so that it can pay for public services
income tax
tax cuts
duty

data.chText: 指购物税项，尤指进口货物交纳的关税：
data.enText: a tax that you pay on things that you buy, especially those that you bring into a country

data.chText: 该公司须为所有进口货物缴纳关税。
data.enText: The company has to pay customs duties on all imports.
customs
tax that is paid when goods are brought in from other countries
tariff
a tax that is paid on goods coming into or going out of a country

data.chText: 国外进口货物当时按普通税率征税。
data.enText: A general tariff was imposed on foreign imports.
levy
an extra amount of money that has to be paid, especially as a tax to the government

data.chText: 对进口石油征收的税款
data.enText: a levy on oil imports
excise
a tax that is paid on some goods made, sold or used within a country
There has been a sharp increase in vehicle excise.

data.chText: 以上各词均指货品税。excise指国内货品税；customs指进口货品税；tariff指常为使国内工业免遭廉价进口商品的冲击，对进出口商品征收的关税；duty较笼统，指进口货品税或国内货品税均可；levy在这组词中最笼统，可指任何种类的税或收费。
data.enText: These are all words for taxes on goods. Excise is for goods sold within a country. Customs is for goods brought into a country. Tariffs are on goods going into or coming out of a country, often in order to protect industry from cheap imports. Duty is more general and can be a customs or excise tax. Levy is the most general of all and can be any sort of tax or charge.

ex.chText: 员工没有义务购买本公司生产的产品。
ex.enText: Employees are under no obligation to buy any products from their own company.

ex.chText: 他们不得不履行条约规定的义务。
ex.enText: They have to fulfil the obligations imposed on them by the treaties.

ex.chText: 他出于责任感而替她保守秘密。
ex.enText: He kept the secret for her out of a sense of obligation.

ex.chText: 事实上，履行这些义务需要更多的财力。
ex.enText: In fact, greater resources are needed to meet these obligations.

synonyms.bx: 指法规、合同等规定的该做或不该做的事，含强制之意；也指因诺言、誓言等而必须要做的事。

ex.chText: 该公司对质量作出承诺。
ex.enText: The company made a commitment to quality.

ex.chText: 88%的受访者表示婚姻应该是一辈子的承诺。
ex.enText: 88 percent of respondents said marriage should be a lifelong commit-ment.
She's got a lot of commitments.

synonyms.bx: 指会去做某事的保证或保证去做的事情。

ex.chText: 他觉得帮助邻居是他的责任。
ex.enText: He feels it is his duty to help his neighbors.

ex.chText: 她从小就被教育要有强烈的道德责任感。
ex.enText: She was brought up to have a strong sense of moral duty.

ex.chText: 切勿忘记你对祖国应尽的义务。
ex.enText: Never forget your duty to your motherland.

ex.chText: 他的职责包括清理草坪。
ex.enText: His duties included sweeping the lawn.

synonyms.bx: 指在道义或法律上应尽的本分，强调自觉性；也指工作职责，此时通常用复数。

ex.chText: 你准备好在新的工作岗位上履行职责了吗？
ex.enText: Are you ready to perform your functions in your new job?

ex.chText: 这个新成立的部门的职能是什么？
ex.enText: What's the function of this newly founded department?

synonyms.bx: 指某人的工作职责或某事物的职能或功用。

ex.chText: 一般而言，升职意味着更多的薪水和更大的责任。
ex.enText: Generally speaking, a promotion means higher salary and more responsibility.

ex.chText: 如有任何变动，你有责任通知他们。
ex.enText: It's your responsibility to inform them of any changes.

ex.chText: 谁应该为这场政治危机负全责？
ex.enText: Who should accept full responsibility for the political crisis?

ex.chText: 她的职责包括分发宣传册和接听电话。
ex.enText: Her responsibilities include handing out brochures and answering the phone.

synonyms.bx: 指管控某人或某事物的责任、对不良事件所负的责任或工作职责，强调对他人的责任。

tr: work that you are obliged to perform for moral or legal reasons
the social force that binds you to the courses of action demanded by that force
every possession, a duty"- John D.Rockefeller Jr
example: we must instill a sense of duty in our children

tr: a government tax on imports or exports
example: they signed a treaty to lower duties on trade between their countries

value.def: Duty is work that you have to do for your job.

example.ex: Staff must report for duty at their normal place of work...
example.tran: 职员必须在平时上班的地方签到。

example.ex: My duty is to look after the animals.
example.tran: 我的责任就是照看这些动物。

value.def: Your duties are tasks which you have to do because they are part of your job.

example.ex: I carried out my duties conscientiously...
example.tran: 我一丝不苟地履行我的职责。

example.ex: He was relieved of his duties as presidential adviser.
example.tran: 他被撤销了总统顾问一职。

value.def: If you say that something is your duty, you believe that you ought to do it because it is your responsibility.

example.ex: I consider it my duty to write to you and thank you.
example.tran: 我认为写信向你表达谢意是我的责任。

value.def: Duties are taxes which you pay to the government on goods that you buy.

example.tran: 进口税的平均水平仍然在 30%。

example.ex: They are pressing the Chancellor to reduce excise duty on beer.
example.tran: 他们正给总理施压，要求降低啤酒的消费税。

value.def: If someone such as a policeman or a nurse is off duty, they are not working. If someone is on duty, they are working.

example.ex: Four officers were told to go off duty and rest at home...
example.tran: 四名官员已经被通知停职在家休整。

example.ex: There were 2,250 policemen on duty in and around the stadium...
example.tran: 在体育场内及周边有 2,250 名警察在值勤。

example.ex: Extra staff had been put on duty.
